ite-Green\"), Hungary\n* {{flagof|Tamil Eelam|name=''Puli Kodi''}} (\"Tiger flag\"), Tamil Eelam\n\n==Q==\n* {{flagof|Taiwan|name=\u9752\u5929\u3001\u767d\u65e5\u3001\u6eff\u5730\u7d05}} (''Q\u012bng Ti\u0101n, B\u00e1i R\u00ec, M\u01cen D\u00ec H\u00f3ng'' [\"Blue Sky, White Sun, Red Field\"]), Taiwan\n\n==R==\n* {{flagof|South Africa|name=''The Rainbow Flag'', ''Unity Flag'', or ''Interim Flag''}} (all unofficial), South Africa\n* {{flagof|image=ICA flag.svg}} [[Rainbow flag]], there are several independent rainbow flags in use today, the most widely known worldwide is the pride flag representing gay pride, while the peace flag is especially popular in Italy and the cooperative flag symbolizes the international co-operative movement.\n* {{flagof|United States|name=''Red, White and Blue''}}, United States\n* {{flagof|North Korea|name=''Ramhongsaek Konghwagukgi''}} (\"Indigo and Red Flag of the Republic\"), North Korea\n* {{flagof|United Kingdom|variant=civil|link=Red Ensign|name=''Red Ensign'' or ''Red Duster''}}, the [[civil ensign]] of the United Kingdom\n*{{flagof|Valencia|name=''Reial senyera''}} (\"Royal flag\"), Valencia\n* {{flagof|Soviet Union|name=''\u041a\u0440\u0430\u0441\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0444\u043b\u0430\u0433 \u0421\u0421\u0421\u0420''}} (''Krasnyy flag SSSR'') (\"Red Flag USSR\"), Soviet Union\n* {{flagof|Russia|name=''\u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0442\u0440\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0440''}} (''Rosiiski Trikolor'') (\"Russian Three Colours\"), Russia\n* {{flagof|Spain|name=''Rojigualda''}} (\"Red-weld\"), Spain\n* {{flagof|Austria|name=''Rot-Weiss-Rot''}} (\"Red-white-red\"), Austria\n* {{flagof|Luxembourg|variant=civil|name=''De Roude L\u00e9iw''}} (\"Red Lion\"), civil ensign of Luxembourg\n* {{flagof|Belarus|name=''\u0420\u0443\u0447\u043d\u0456\u043a''}} (''Ru\u010dnik''), Belarus\n\n==S==\n* {{flagof|Scotland|name=''Saint Andrew's Cross'' or ''The Saltire''}}, Scotland\n* {{flagof|England|link=}} ''[[Saint George's Cross]]'', England\n* {{flagof|Devon|name=''Saint Petroc's Flag''}}, Devon\n* {{flagof|Laos|name=''Sam Si''}} (\"Tricolor\"), Laos\n* {{flagof|Latvia|name=''Sarkanbaltsarkanais karogs''}} (\"Red-white-red flag\"), Latvia\n* {{flagof|Indonesia|name=''Sang Saka Merah Putih''}} (\"The Red White\"), Indonesia\n* {{flagof|Macedonia|variant=1992|section=\"Vergina Flag\" (1992\u20131995)|name=''\u0405\u0432\u0435\u0437\u0434\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043e\u0434 \u041a\u0443\u0442\u043b\u0435\u0448''}} (\"[[Vergina Sun|Sun of Kutle\u0161]]'), Republic of Macedonia (historical flag)\n* {{flagof|Germany|name=''Schwarz-Rot-Gold''}} (\"Black-red-gold\"), Germany\n* {{flagof|image=Flag of the German Empire.svg}} ''[[Schwarz-Wei\u00df-Rot]]'' (\"Black-white-red\"), German Empire\n* {{flagof|Iran|name=''Seh-ye Rang-ye Beyraq''}} ('\"Tricolor\"), Iran\n* {{flagof|Catalonia|link=Senyera|name=''Senyera''}}, [[Alghero]] and [[Catalonia]]\n* {{flagof|Iran|variant=1964|section=Post-Constitutional Revolution|name=''Shir-o-Khorshid''}} ('The lion and the sun\"), Iran (historical flag)\n* {{flagof|Albania|name=''Shqiponja Dykrenare''}} (\"The two-headed eagle\"), Albania\n* {{flagof|Estonia|name=''Sinimustvalge''}} (\"Blue-black-white\"), Estonia\n* {{flagof|Finland|name=''Siniristilippu''}} (\"Blue Cross Flag\"), Finland\n* {{flagof|Sri Lanka |name=''Sinha Flag''}} (\"Lion Flag\"), Sri Lanka\n* {{flagof|Tibet|name=''Snow lion flag''}}, Tibet\n* {{flagof|Confederate States of America|name=''Southern Cross''}}, Confederate States ([[Southern Cross (disambiguation)|other meanings]])\n* {{flagof|Australia|name=''Southern Cross Flag''}}, Australia\n* {{flagof|New Zealand|name=''Southern Cross Flag''}}, New Zealand\n* {{flagof|Confederate States of America|variant=1861|name=''Stars and Bars''}}, Confederate States\n* {{flagof|United States|name=''Stars and Stripes''}}, United States\n* {{flagof|United States|1795|link=Star-Spangled Banner (flag)|name=''Star-Spangled Banner''}},{{efn|Origi