id Stoll]]\n*[[John Styles]]\n*[[Dudley Sutton]]\n*[[Ingrid Sylvester]]\n'''T'''\n*[[Larry Taylor (actor)|Larry Taylor]]\n*[[Nigel Terry]]\n*[[Tony Thawnton]]\n*[[Hilary Tindall]]\n*[[John A. Tinn]]\n*[[Frederick Treves (actor)|Frederick Treves]]\n'''V'''\n*[[Colin Vancao]]\n*[[Peter Vaughan]]\n*[[Sue Vaughan]]\n*[[Don Vernon]]\n'''W'''\n*[[John Walker (actor)|John Walker]]\n*[[Gary Watson]]\n*[[Kenneth Watson]]\n*[[David Webb (anti-censorship campaigner)|David Webb]]\n*[[Timothy West]]\n*[[Phillip Weston]]\n*[[Les White (actor)|Les White]]\n*[[Frank Windsor]]\n*[[Beverly Winn]]\n*[[Hilary Wontner]]\n*[[Betty Woolfe]]\n*[[Jack Woolgar]]\n*[[Katya Wyeth]]\n'''Y'''\n*[[Jeremy Young]]\n*[[Raymond Young]]\n'''Z'''\n*[[Nick Zaran]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n{{hidden end}}\n\n==Episode list==\n\nAirdates given here are for [[LWT]] (London). It was the only ITV station to screen all 26 episodes without breaks in transmission. Other [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] regions varied airdates and transmission order.\n\nFilming took place between May 1968 and July 1969.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-style=\"color:black\"\n! style=\"background: #ACE5EE;\"|Episode #\n! style=\"background: #ACE5EE;\"|Prod #\n! style=\"background: #ACE5EE;\"|Title\n! style=\"background: #ACE5EE;\"|Directed by\n! style=\"background: #ACE5EE;\"|Written by\n! style=\"background: #ACE5EE;\"|Original&nbsp;airdate\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=1\n |EpisodeNumber2=4001\n |Title=[[My Late Lamented Friend and Partner]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1969|9|21|df=y}}\n |WrittenBy=[[Ralph Smart]]\n |DirectedBy=[[Cyril Frankel]]\n |ShortSummary= Private Investigator Marty Hopkirk is murdered by the husband of a client but returns as a [[ghost]] to help his business partner Jeff Randall bring the man responsible for his murder to justice.\n|LineColor=BFF0FF\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber=2\n |EpisodeNumber2=4022\n |Title=[[A Disturbing Case]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|1969|9|28|df=y}}\n |Written